00:33:47,525 --> 00:33:49,459
That'll be fine. Poncho.

258
00:33:58,369 --> 00:33:59,301
Here.

259
00:34:01,406 --> 00:34:04,102
-How about taking these things off?
-No.

260
00:34:04,375 --> 00:34:05,307
We'll make better time.

261
00:34:06,778 --> 00:34:08,746
You in a hurry to get there?

262
00:34:08,746 --> 00:34:11,214
Right now, l'd settle
for free hands.

263
00:34:12,016 --> 00:34:13,540
Might give you ideas.

264
00:34:14,152 --> 00:34:16,086
l've seen your shooting, mister.

265
00:34:17,188 --> 00:34:19,122
Man, you've got me
scared to death.

266
00:34:20,358 --> 00:34:21,290
How about some papers?

267
00:34:31,569 --> 00:34:33,304
What are you going to do about it?

268
00:34:33,304 --> 00:34:34,669
You're going to have to
stop it right now.

269
00:34:35,873 --> 00:34:37,306
Can l get off my horse?

270
00:34:38,342 --> 00:34:39,274
Yeah.

271
00:35:08,906 --> 00:35:10,840
He go very comfortably?

272
00:35:15,980 --> 00:35:18,312
l guess so. How much
for the poncho?

273
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:24,010
He wants 10, give him 5.

274
00:35:28,192 --> 00:35:29,819
Here, is that all right?

275
00:35:32,930 --> 00:35:35,125
Tell him to hold the girl here.

276
00:36:20,912 --> 00:36:23,574
Man, when l make a mistake,
l make it good.

277
00:36:25,583 --> 00:36:28,279
l should have killed you
back in Cerralvo.

278
00:36:30,221 --> 00:36:33,019
My second mistake was leaving
Elena behind.

279
00:36:35,459 --> 00:36:37,427
You know, l miss her already.

280
00:36:39,130 --> 00:36:41,064
-Hold it. Hold up.
-What's the matter?

281
00:36:46,571 --> 00:36:48,402
-Apaches.
-Yeah.

282
00:36:50,241 --> 00:36:53,176
Just keep looking at them. They'll
come out in their own time.

283
00:36:54,378 --> 00:36:55,310
We'll wait.

284
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:58,414
l've got plenty of time, man.

285
00:37:34,619 --> 00:37:37,110
-You get a whiff of that liquor?
-Yeah.

286
00:37:38,289 --> 00:37:40,223
l wonder where they've been.

287
00:37:40,558 --> 00:37:42,492
You're the lawman. Why
don't you ask them?

288
00:37:43,027 --> 00:37:45,257
When you ask questions, you
gotta wait for answers.

289
00:37:45,363 --> 00:37:47,297
My job's to take you back
to Scottsville.

290
00:37:51,435 --> 00:37:54,404
All right, let's move out
of here, slow-like.

291
00:38:10,655 --> 00:38:11,587
Wait a minute.

292
00:38:19,397 --> 00:38:21,331
Looks like we shook them.

293
00:38:21,966 --> 00:38:23,729
You afraid of lndians?

294
00:38:24,769 --> 00:38:26,404
l'm respectful of any man who's
got enough liquor...

295
00:38:26,404 --> 00:38:28,372
in him to make him kill.

296
00:38:29,073 --> 00:38:32,304
Seems to me l've heard something
like that about you.

297
00:38:32,410 --> 00:38:35,573
-l never killed a man with liquor.
-Yeah? l heard different.

298
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:37,713
You heard lies.

299
00:38:38,716 --> 00:38:39,876
How far to Scottsville?

300
00:38:40,117 --> 00:38:42,085
Riding easy, another three days.

301
00:38:42,820 --> 00:38:44,754
l could sure use some fresh meat.

302
00:38:45,256 --> 00:38:47,190
Maybe l can get some along the way.

303
00:38:48,893 --> 00:38:51,195
You do some of that fancy
shooting of yours.

304
00:38:51,195 --> 00:38:53,129
Man, l'd sure like to watch that.

305
00:39:03,641 --> 00:39:05,575
How do you like your rabbit,
Kallen?

306
00:39:05,876 --> 00:39:06,808
Raw.

307
00:39:11,682 --> 00:39:13,616
l wonder what's ailing him?

308
00:39:14,251 --> 00:39:15,741
Maybe he smells that rabbit.

309
00:39:26,430 --> 00:39:27,362
-Hamish.
-Yeah.

310
00:39:30,234 --> 00:39:32,725
l don't think we shook
those lndians.

311
00:39:42,947 --> 00:39:45,211
What are you going to do about it?

312
00:39:45,349 --> 00:39:46,281
Nothing.

313
00:39:52,957 --> 00:39:55,425
l know what they're like.
We're in trouble.

314
00:39:56,460 --> 00:39:58,394
You afraid of lndians?

315
00:39:59,296 --> 00:40:01,230
No more than you're afraid of me.

316
00:40:04,001 --> 00:40:05,935
The meat's burning. Take it off.

317
00:40:07,638 --> 00:40:09,230
l get in the light, they
pick me off.

318
00:40:10,241 --> 00:40:11,606
ls that what you want?

319
00:40:11,675 --> 00:40:13,040
That's the general idea, l guess.

320
00:40:13,811 --> 00:40:14,743
Not to me, it ain't.

321
00:40:15,279 --> 00:40:18,214
The meat's burning, and l don't
like my meat burnt. Take it off.

322
00:40:29,393 --> 00:40:31,095
All right, that's far enough.

323
00:40:31,095 --> 00:40:32,027
Come on.

324
00:40:32,630 --> 00:40:35,121
lt's a fine time to be suspicious.

325
00:40:36,667 --> 00:40:37,599
Here.

326
00:40:41,138 --> 00:40:42,662
Give me a knife to cut it.

327
00:40:42,740 --> 00:40:44,207
Use your teeth.

328
00:40:52,683 --> 00:40:54,251
lf l decide to go back
to Scottsville,...

329
00:40:54,251 --> 00:40:55,479
what are my chances?

330
00:40:57,588 --> 00:40:58,722
l'm not a jury.

331
00:40:58,722 --> 00:41:01,657
Those two in Scottsville, that
was self-defense.

332
00:41:02,593 --> 00:41:05,255
l'd taken them the night
before at cards.

333
00:41:05,463 --> 00:41:07,397
They claimed l was cheating.

334
00:41:08,966 --> 00:41:12,163
Next morning, l was getting a
shave, they came in.

335
00:41:12,570 --> 00:41:14,504
l was faster, that's all.

336
00:41:17,608 --> 00:41:18,540
You hear that?

337
00:41:23,380 --> 00:41:24,278
l heard it.

338
00:41:24,815 --> 00:41:26,550
You stay put.

339
00:41:26,550 --> 00:41:28,484
l'm going to go out
and take a look.

340
00:41:29,687 --> 00:41:31,355
You leaving me without a gun?

341
00:41:31,355 --> 00:41:34,518
You just stay put, and if you get
any ideas about getting away...

342
00:41:34,658 --> 00:41:36,360
if the lndians don't
kill you, l will.

343
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:37,918
-Hamish...
-Shut up!

344
00:42:28,345 --> 00:42:29,277
What'd you find?

345
00:42:31,882 --> 00:42:33,816
They're out there, all right.

346
00:42:38,556 --> 00:42:39,488
Hamish...

347
00:42:40,624 --> 00:42:42,216
l'd rather take my chances
with the lndians,...

348
00:42:43,093 --> 00:42:44,651
than you in Scottsville.

349
00:42:46,430 --> 00:42:47,362
l'm getting out.

350
00:42:54,071 --> 00:42:57,234
All right, drop your gun. Easy.

351
00:42:58,509 --> 00:43:00,238
l swear l'll plug you.

352
00:43:00,711 --> 00:43:03,509
You didn't think l'd leave it
loaded, did you?

353
00:43:19,330 --> 00:43:21,093
You're foxy, mister.

354
00:43:23,534 --> 00:43:25,365
l'm learning about you.

355
00:43:33,210 --> 00:43:34,677
Take your time.

356
00:43:43,220 --> 00:43:44,585
Look at that.

357
00:43:45,889 --> 00:43:47,618
Guess l go first.

358
00:44:28,699 --> 00:44:30,667
There's a house down there.

359
00:44:30,801 --> 00:44:31,733
Come on.

360
00:44:33,303 --> 00:44:35,032
You mean, you ain't going down?

361
00:44:35,272 --> 00:44:36,204
lt's out of the way.

362
00:44:37,574 --> 00:44:40,065
You can shoot me if you want,
l'm going down.

363
00:44:40,177 --> 00:44:42,611
l'm thirsty, l'm hungry
and l'm tired.

364
00:44:44,448 --> 00:44:46,382
-You think l'm not?
-That's your worry.

365
00:45:10,874 --> 00:45:12,808
Why don't you ask first?

366
00:45:14,712 --> 00:45:15,644
Hello.

367
00:45:48,679 --> 00:45:50,078
Those Apaches.

368
00:46:04,194 --> 00:46:05,821
They killed a kid.

369
00:46:16,874 --> 00:46:17,806
-Kallen!

370
00:46:19,543 --> 00:46:20,532
-Kallen!
-What?

371
00:46:22,946 --> 00:46:24,880
We'll bury them out back.

372
00:46:28,285 --> 00:46:30,150
That's all they are to you.

373
00:46:31,688 --> 00:46:33,383
Something dead.

374
00:46:34,591 --> 00:46:36,320
You got nothing in you at all.

375
00:46:36,460 --> 00:46:37,392
Shut up!

376
00:46:39,463 --> 00:46:41,397
Don't tell me about the dead.

377
00:46:51,008 --> 00:46:52,942
We'll bury them out back.

378
00:47:30,447 --> 00:47:32,312
''Now l lay me down to sleep.

379
00:47:33,851 --> 00:47:34,783
''l beg...

380
00:47:35,819 --> 00:47:37,753
''the Lord my soul to keep.

381
00:47:39,790 --> 00:47:42,088
''lf l should die before l wake...

382
00:47:50,434 --> 00:47:52,368
''l pray the Lord my soul...''

383
00:47:54,404 --> 00:47:56,338
''l pray the Lord my soul to take.''

384
00:47:57,274 --> 00:47:58,206
Amen.

385
00:48:29,439 --> 00:48:31,339
Where'd it come from?

386
00:48:32,242 --> 00:48:34,335
Off in the trees, over
there, l think.

387
00:48:36,380 --> 00:48:37,813
Let's head for the ditch.

388
00:48:57,234 --> 00:48:58,826
-You all right?
-Sure.

389
00:49:01,972 --> 00:49:03,701
-The horses.
-Stay down!

390
00:49:03,807 --> 00:49:06,410
-l'm gonna save my horse!
-We've gotta save our skins!

391
00:49:06,410 --> 00:49:07,638
You're yellow.

392
00:49:10,580 --> 00:49:13,515
We're going to have to make a run
for the cabin. Go on.

393
00:49:45,983 --> 00:49:48,577
Now what, General? You've
got us stuck.

394
00:49:51,355 --> 00:49:53,323
You quit riding me.

395
00:49:53,323 --> 00:49:55,625
l've had enough out of you.
l can't take anymore.

396
00:49:55,625 --> 00:49:57,594
You quit riding me! Keep
your mouth shut!

397
00:49:57,594 --> 00:49:58,862
You're brave with that gun.

398
00:49:58,862 --> 00:50:00,796
Why didn't you shoot back when
you had the chance?

399
00:50:00,964 --> 00:50:04,263
You could have saved the horses!
You know what? You're yellow!

400
00:50:04,801 --> 00:50:07,031
You've got a streak a mile wide.

401
00:50:38,068 --> 00:50:40,434
l think one of the horses is back.

402
00:50:43,173 --> 00:50:44,504
lt's yours.

403
00:50:47,044 --> 00:50:49,069
-Where you going?
-To get my horse.

404
00:51:06,663 --> 00:51:07,595
Come on.

405
00:51:13,703 --> 00:51:16,069
-What are you going to do?
-He's coming in with me.

406
00:51:28,852 --> 00:51:29,784
Here.

407
00:51:31,922 --> 00:51:33,856
You never had it so good.

408
00:51:43,900 --> 00:51:45,834
What are you looking for?

409
00:51:46,403 --> 00:51:48,337
For a gun to kill you with.

410
00:51:59,749 --> 00:52:00,841
-Hamish.
-What?

411
00:52:01,718 --> 00:52:02,548
-O quê?

412
00:52:12,062 --> 00:52:15,691
Why would anybody come to a place
like this to raise a kid?

413
00:52:17,234 --> 00:52:18,531
Lots of room, maybe.

414
00:52:19,436 --> 00:52:20,368
There are reasons.

415
00:52:26,176 --> 00:52:28,110
l guess a kid makes a difference
in a place.

416
00:52:32,983 --> 00:52:35,474
You wouldn't know about that.

417
00:52:37,888 --> 00:52:39,617
That's right.

418
00:52:40,190 --> 00:52:43,125
l got a wife who can't have any kids,
'cause she lost her first one.

419
00:52:50,534 --> 00:52:52,468
What's the matter, you
hear something?

420
00:52:53,236 --> 00:52:54,168
lt's starting to rain.

421
00:52:56,840 --> 00:52:59,308
l always did like the
sound of rain.

422
00:53:02,412 --> 00:53:04,346
l wonder if it's raining
back at Cerralvo.

423
00:53:07,684 --> 00:53:09,618
Elena's sure gonna be mad.

424
00:53:10,020 --> 00:53:11,954
l never did fix the roof.

425
00:53:13,957 --> 00:53:16,755
That's the second thing l do
when l get back.

426
00:53:18,628 --> 00:53:21,563
Man, a bed's sure going
to feel good tonight.

427
00:53:26,636 --> 00:53:27,568
What are you going to do?

428
00:53:28,471 --> 00:53:31,875
l need sleep. l need it bad.
l know l won't get any...

429
00:53:31,875 --> 00:53:34,810
but l don't want to worry about
you, so l'm gonna tie you up.

430
00:53:35,045 --> 00:53:36,603
Come on, not tonight.

431
00:53:36,713 --> 00:53:38,271
l don't trust you.

432
00:53:38,448 --> 00:53:40,382
Here, put this through your feet.

433
00:55:07,470 --> 00:55:10,837
l could save the law a bother by
throwing you to the lndians right

434
00:55:11,074 --> 00:55:15,238
or killing you myself, but you're
going to stand trial.

435
00:55:16,313 --> 00:55:18,281
lf l have to drag you back at the
end of a rope,...

436
00:55:18,281 --> 00:55:20,146
you're gonna stand trial.

437
00:55:32,662 --> 00:55:34,323
All right, lead him out.

438
00:55:37,600 --> 00:55:38,532
Come on.

439
00:55:47,410 --> 00:55:48,611
What's the matter?

440
00:55:48,611 --> 00:55:51,478
-There's one over there, by the
woodshed. Where?

441
00:55:52,782 --> 00:55:54,716
He ducked behind it now.

442
00:56:09,733 --> 00:56:11,667
We're going to help you out.

443
00:56:26,516 --> 00:56:27,574
Look, kid.

444
00:56:27,650 --> 00:56:30,585
We're not going to hurt you.
We're your friends.

445
00:56:32,322 --> 00:56:35,621
You know, for a minute, l...

446
00:56:37,994 --> 00:56:39,461
Me, too.

447
00:56:42,031 --> 00:56:43,498
Twins, l guess.

448
00:56:46,503 --> 00:56:48,198
They ain't here now.

449
00:56:49,506 --> 00:56:50,404
They've gone.

450
00:56:54,043 --> 00:56:55,601
What's your name?

451
00:56:56,246 --> 00:56:59,113
-What's your name, kid?
-Don't be scared of him.

452
00:57:00,216 --> 00:57:01,148
What's your name?

453
00:57:03,153 --> 00:57:04,051
l'm your friend.

454
00:57:05,255 --> 00:57:06,187
Do you know my name?

455
00:57:06,923 --> 00:57:08,857
My name's Roberto.

456
00:57:10,627 --> 00:57:12,492
That means ''Bob.''

457
00:57:16,666 --> 00:57:17,598
Come on.

458
00:57:17,934 --> 00:57:19,868
Cat got your tongue or something?

459
00:57:20,403 --> 00:57:21,335
Come on.

460
00:57:23,339 --> 00:57:24,271
Can't you talk?

461
00:57:34,951 --> 00:57:36,384
l don't know...

462
00:57:42,091 --> 00:57:44,924
-You suppose she saw what
happened? -Probably.

463
00:57:46,362 --> 00:57:48,387
lt's a bad thing for a kid to see.

464
00:57:50,066 --> 00:57:52,967
l wish she'd talk or
cry or something.

465
00:57:54,003 --> 00:57:56,801
What'll we do? Three of us can't
get out of here on the horse.

466
00:57:56,873 --> 00:57:59,205
-You can't leave her here!
-l know that!

467
00:58:01,978 --> 00:58:03,605
Come on, have a biscuit.

468
00:58:03,680 --> 00:58:04,612
ls that nag of yours any good?

469
00:58:05,215 --> 00:58:07,012
He came back, didn't he?

470
00:58:07,283 --> 00:58:08,511
lf we hitched him to
the buckboard...

471
00:58:09,886 --> 00:58:13,617
you put her in the back, and you
drove, do you think he'd pull it?

472
00:58:16,125 --> 00:58:18,059
What have we got to lose
except my horse?

473
00:58:18,495 --> 00:58:19,427
Come on.

474
00:58:19,596 --> 00:58:21,530
All right, get some
things for her.

475
00:58:36,279 --> 00:58:37,769
Here, this is for you.

476
00:58:38,381 --> 00:58:40,144
Come on. You put it on.

477
00:58:43,486 --> 00:58:45,420
l'll get you something to eat.

478
00:58:55,899 --> 00:58:57,389
Come on!

479
00:59:01,237 --> 00:59:03,364
Come on, baby. Here.

480
00:59:04,474 --> 00:59:07,409
You're going to need this.
Gets cold at night.

481
00:59:09,345 --> 00:59:10,243
Hey, look.

482
00:59:11,414 --> 00:59:12,346
Come on.

483
00:59:16,052 --> 00:59:17,986
-Hurry it up, Kallen.
-Coming.

484
00:59:24,193 --> 00:59:25,592
All right, kid, you stay down.

485
01:00:07,270 --> 01:00:09,204
We can't go on like this.

486
01:00:11,441 --> 01:00:13,375
We'll have to drop this wagon.

487
01:00:15,078 --> 01:00:16,010
l don't get it.

488
01:00:16,079 --> 01:00:19,014
Why didn't they follow us when
we first left the cabin?

489
01:00:20,183 --> 01:00:21,115
Why should they?

490
01:00:21,584 --> 01:00:23,518
How far can we get, like this?

491
01:00:23,586 --> 01:00:26,556
We're out in the open anyway. At
least we can see them coming.

492
01:00:26,556 --> 01:00:27,614
l'm not worried.

493
01:00:28,057 --> 01:00:29,251
You shoot real good.

494
01:00:29,959 --> 01:00:31,119
l want to make some cover
before night.

495
01:00:31,227 --> 01:00:32,489
Come on, let me have it.

496
01:00:33,029 --> 01:00:35,156
-l gotta feed the kid.
-Feed her.

497
01:00:37,433 --> 01:00:38,365
Look, kid.

498
01:00:39,402 --> 01:00:40,596
Will you eat something?

499
01:00:41,704 --> 01:00:44,639
Come on. You haven't eaten
for two days.

500
01:00:46,209 --> 01:00:47,267
lt'll make you grow big.

501
01:00:47,410 --> 01:00:49,105
Come on. Get it inside her.

502
01:00:49,312 --> 01:00:51,781
She ain't no hog! You don't
feed a kid like a hog!

503
01:00:51,781 --> 01:00:53,214
All right, feed her then.

504
01:00:53,282 --> 01:00:55,216
Kid, please eat something.

505
01:00:55,852 --> 01:00:57,376
Come on, come on.

506
01:00:58,421 --> 01:01:01,356
Eat this! l don't want it wasted!
Now eat it.

507
01:01:02,125 --> 01:01:04,286
You have a nice way with kids.

508
01:01:09,098 --> 01:01:11,965
l'm taking my problems
out on her, l guess.

509
01:01:18,474 --> 01:01:19,406
Come on, now.

510
01:01:19,475 --> 01:01:21,409
Will you do it for me?

511
01:01:21,577 --> 01:01:22,544
lt tastes real good.

512
01:01:23,312 --> 01:01:25,303
Come on. That's it.

513
01:01:27,016 --> 01:01:28,677
Come on, eat it.

514
01:01:29,252 --> 01:01:30,184
That's a girl!

515
01:01:32,255 --> 01:01:34,723
Come on. l'll let you
ride my horse.

516
01:01:35,892 --> 01:01:36,824
That's it.

517
01:01:40,530 --> 01:01:41,462
Tastes good?

518
01:01:50,707 --> 01:01:51,639
All right.

519
01:01:52,608 --> 01:01:53,540
Now, you lead him.

520
